## Origin

> For most of my life, I found myself on the edge of systems rather than comfortably inside them. At the time, I thought this was a personal story. Over time a different question emerged — why do intelligent people repeatedly misunderstand one another even when they appear to agree?
>
> I am not interested in helping people think harder. I am interested in helping people waste less cognition on avoidable misunderstanding.

Independent by circumstance. Rigorous by necessity.  
Following a signal that kept appearing just upstream of where everyone else was looking.

